children.name: llama x
children.definition: llama a large south american animal with a long neck and long hair, and which is often kept for its meat, milk, fur and to carry heavy loads : lạc đà không bướu

children.name: camel b1
children.definition: camel a large animal with a long neck, that lives in the desert and has one or two humps (= large raised areas of flesh) on its back : lạc đà

children.name: dromedary x
children.definition: dromedary a type of camel (= a large animal that lives in the desert) with one hump (= raised area) on its back : lạc đà một bướu

children.name: polecat x
children.definition: polecatnounchồn hôi
examples: a smallfiercewild animal that lives ineurope, asia and north africa, which has dark brown fur and a strong, unpleasant smell

children.name: skunk x
children.definition: skunknounchồn hôi
examples: a small black and white north american animal that makes a strong unpleasant smell as a defence when it is attacked

children.name: weasel x
children.definition: weasel a small mammal with reddish brown fur and a long body, which can kill other small animals such as mice and birds for food : con chồn

children.name: sloth x
children.definition: sloth a mammal that moves slowly and lives in trees:con lười
examples: sloths live in central and south america.

children.name: badger x
children.definition: badgernoun con lửng
examples: an animal with greyish brown fur, a black and white head and a pointed face, which lives underground and comes out to feed at night

children.name: ferret x
children.definition: ferretnounchồn sương
examples: a small yellowish-white animal with a long body, bred for hunting rabbits and other small animals

children.name: stoat x
children.definition: stoatnounchồn ecmin
examples: a small thin animal which has brown fur in summer and white fur in winter

children.name: mammoth x
children.definition: mammoth a type of large elephant covered in hair that had tusks and no longer exists : voi cổ, voi ma-mút

children.name: rhinoceros x
children.definition: rhinoceros(informalrhino)  a very large thick-skinned animal from africa or asia, which has one or two horns on its nose : tê giác
examples: a population of black/ white rhinoceros

children.name: elephant a2
children.definition: elephant a very large grey mammal which has a trunk (= long nose) with which it can pick things up : con voi

children.name: kangaroo b1
children.definition: kangaroo (australian informalroo) a large australian mammal with a long stiff tail, short front legs and long powerful back legs on which it moves by jumping

children.name: quokka x
children.definition: quokka a small wallaby (= an animal with a long tail and strong legs for jumping with) which in the past existed in great numbers in western australia : căng-gu-ru đuôi ngắn

children.name: wallaby x
children.definition: wallaby an animal found in australia and new guinea which is like a smallkangaroo, and has strong back legs for jumping with and a long tail

children.name: mongoose x
children.definition: mongoose a small tropical animal with a long tail which eats snakes, rats and birds' eggs : cầy mangut

children.name: civet x
children.definition: civet a small animal like a cat from africa and southern asia : cầy hương

children.name: aardvark x
children.definition: aardvark an african mammal with a long nose and large ears which lives underground and eats insects : lợn đất

children.name: anteater x
children.definition: anteater a mammal which eats ants or termites and has no teeth, a long nose and tongue : thú ăn kiến

children.name: platypus x
children.definition: platypus/ duck-billed platypus an australian river mammal with a wide beak whose young are born from eggs : rái mỏ vịt; thú mỏ vịt

children.name: fruit bat x
children.definition: fruit bat/ flying fox a large flying mammal which eats fruit and lives in warm or hot countries : dơi ăn quả

children.name: bat b1
children.definition: bat a small animal like a mouse with wings that flies at night : dơi

children.name: vampire bat x
children.definition: vampire bat a small central and south american flying animal which sucks blood from other animals : dơi quỷ

children.name: porcupine x
children.definition: porcupine an animal with a protective covering of long sharp quills (= stiff hairs like needles) on its back : con nhím

children.name: hippopotamus x
children.definition: hippopotamus(informalhippo)  a very large animal with short legs and thick, dark grey skin which lives near water in africa : lợn nước, hà mã

children.name: otter x
children.definition: otter a mammal with four legs and short brown fur which swims well and eats fish : con rái cá

children.name: giraffe b1
children.definition: giraffe a large african animal with a very long neck and long legs: hươu cao cổ

children.name: hedgehog x
children.definition: hedgehog a small brown european animal whose body is round and covered with sharp needle-like spines : nhím nhỏ

children.name: koala x
children.definition: koala/ koala bear an australian animal which lives in trees and looks like a small bear with grey fur : gấu túi

children.name: bear b2
children.definition: bear a large, strong wild mammal with a thick fur coat that lives especially in colder parts of europe, asia and north america : gấu

children.name: panda x
children.definition: panda a large black and white mammal similar to a bear, that lives in forests in china : gấu trúc

children.name: polar bear b2
children.definition: polar bear a bear with white fur that lives near the north pole : gấu bắc cực

children.name: racoon x
children.definition: raccoon/ racoon mainly us informalcoon) a small north american animal with black marks on its face and a long tail with black rings on it : gấu trúc mỹ

children.name: grizzly x
children.definition: grizzly bear/ grizzly a very large greyish brown bear from north america and canada : gấu xám

children.name: pachyderm x
children.definition: pachyderm specialized a type of large mammal with thick skin and hooves, for example an elephant, rhinoceros or hippopotamus : loài da dày
